main event: Two unidentified objects were detected on ground radar at Dover AFB.
interesting points: The sighting lasted under 3 minutes and was observed by both military and civilian personnel., The objects were sighted on radar but subsequently lost to radar., The report concludes that the objects were not balloons and may be possible aircraft., The date of the sighting was November 9, 1955., There is no photographic evidence or images included in the report.
